    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Ewing</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 14.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Légation</hi>, <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 30, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your despatch of the 31st ultimo, No. 12.</p>
                <p>Since my last despatch on the subject the rinderpest has virtually
                            disappeared from Holland. Still I would recommend that for many months
                            to come the precautions against its introduction from this country be
                            continued.</p>
                <p>The authorities have arrived at the conclusion that the only effectual
                            mode to meet the pest is by prompt and unsparing slaughter of cattle in
                            the vicinity where it makes its appearance.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with great respect, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HUGH EWING.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
